5
00:00:15,210 --> 00:00:16,230
Did you smell something?

6
00:00:16,360 --> 00:00:17,470
Omelet?

7
00:00:17,650 --> 00:00:19,570
It's the smell of our memories.

8
00:00:21,410 --> 00:00:23,120
Wear blue tomorrow.

9
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,800
I want us to wear matching shirts.

10
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:27,800
My friend is quite charismatic.

11
00:00:28,110 --> 00:00:29,650
Apart from the prophecy stones,

12
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:31,730
are you also a master of love potions?

13
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:33,970
Haven't you told him yet

14
00:00:33,990 --> 00:00:35,720
that you're not the real sweetheart?

15
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,120
Aren't you gonna be a little humble,

16
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:39,340
Prince Charming?

17
00:00:39,490 --> 00:00:40,710
If I bow down,

18
00:00:40,970 --> 00:00:41,590
will you have me?

19
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:44,550
Is Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master, here?

20
00:00:51,860 --> 00:00:52,780
We've arrived.

21
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,520
Thank you.

22
00:01:30,410 --> 00:01:31,590
Are you back at your place?

23
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,520
Yes, sir.

24
00:01:35,770 --> 00:01:40,220
Are you worried about me or afraid
your bar is missing a fortune teller?

25
00:01:40,990 --> 00:01:41,990
Do you have any idea

26
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,440
who was here looking for you

27
00:01:43,630 --> 00:01:45,350
after you left?

28
00:01:47,050 --> 00:01:48,120
Who?

29
00:01:48,660 --> 00:01:49,670
The real one

30
00:01:49,990 --> 00:01:52,100
has come back to claim what's his.

31
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:05,650
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

32
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:09,740
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

33
00:02:09,770 --> 00:02:14,160
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

34
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:18,220
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

35
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:22,610
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

36
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:26,020
♫Slightly out of line,♫

37
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:30,570
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

38
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:34,910
♫Try answering (if) your world
will cross with mine♫

39
00:02:34,940 --> 00:02:38,990
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

40
00:02:39,010 --> 00:02:44,530
♫And I believe our love has power♫

41
00:02:44,550 --> 00:02:48,350
♫I believe the love of us♫

42
00:02:48,380 --> 00:02:56,300
♫Will realign the stars back to the line
where they should be♫

43
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:31,670
- Here you go.
- Wait, that's Pitcha,

44
00:03:31,810 --> 00:03:33,810
the one who trained
in Korea since childhood.

45
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:36,480
Oh, the boy who got his dream crushed
and didn't debut?

46
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:39,000
He just got injured;
otherwise, he'd have already debuted.

47
00:03:39,490 --> 00:03:40,130
Who is that?

48
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:43,160
The one who's on the news
for debuting as a K-pop idol.

49
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,280
What? Are you a K-pop stan?

50
00:03:45,340 --> 00:03:47,400
I went to school with him
when I was a child.

51
00:03:47,860 --> 00:03:48,860
I remember

52
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,230
that he was teased about

53
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,550
being Business graduate Itthi's sweetheart.

54
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:53,960
Oh!

55
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:57,210
- That handsome poser with a rich daddy?
- Yes!

56
00:03:57,350 --> 00:03:59,800
- There you go.
- Right, I know who he is.

57
00:04:00,290 --> 00:04:01,200
Go say hi.

58
00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:02,310
No way.

59
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:04,250
He's not gonna remember me.

60
00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:14,560
Pitch...

61
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,040
Pitcha...

62
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:18,060
Do you have a table reserved?

63
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:21,120
Hello.

64
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:23,110
Is Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master, here?

65
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,210
Yes.

66
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:27,310
What do I do
if I want my fortune read by Master Ritt?

67
00:04:27,730 --> 00:04:28,800
I'm sorry.

68
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:31,770
Why? Is he fully booked?

69
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:33,360
He was here, but...

70
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:35,380
he just left a minute ago.

71
00:04:36,450 --> 00:04:39,340
Uh, Mister...
Do you want your fortune read, Pitcha?

72
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:44,290
You'll have to wait until tomorrow,
but I'll book you in for the first slot.

73
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:46,320
My name is Ployplern.

74
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:48,350
I'm your fan.

75
00:04:48,550 --> 00:04:50,010
Uh, so...

76
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,800
- Is your ankle all better?
- Then, I'd better come back tomorrow.

77
00:04:53,430 --> 00:04:54,430
What time should I be here?

78
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:56,840
Around 10 or 11 PM.

79
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:59,680
Okay, thank you.

80
00:04:59,930 --> 00:05:00,980
Hold up.

81
00:05:01,330 --> 00:05:03,210
Since you're already here at Magic Move,

82
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:04,910
would you give us the honor of serving you?

83
00:05:05,490 --> 00:05:08,190
If you're here alone,
you can take the bar.

84
00:05:08,260 --> 00:05:10,540
My sister and I will take care of you.

85
00:05:11,940 --> 00:05:12,880
I'm good.

86
00:05:13,990 --> 00:05:15,330
Come on.

87
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:18,840
Consider this
a private fan meeting for her.

88
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:19,880
This girl

89
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,370
is your No.1 fan.

90
00:05:25,090 --> 00:05:26,000
Let's do it tomorrow.

91
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:27,690
Today is fine. Come on.

92
00:05:28,250 --> 00:05:29,050
Here you go.

93
00:05:29,650 --> 00:05:30,730
And I...

94
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:33,140
will prepare a very special drink for you.

95
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:34,900
So...

96
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:37,780
you can drink, right?

97
00:05:37,930 --> 00:05:40,650
Or do you have to ask
for your company's permission first?

98
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:43,040
If you're concerned that someone
might take a photo in secret,

99
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:45,130
- I can serve your drink in an opaque glass.
- I can drink.

100
00:05:49,180 --> 00:05:50,580
Please wait just a second.

101
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,860
Are you hot?
I can turn up the A/C for you.

102
00:05:52,890 --> 00:05:53,590
I'm good.

103
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:55,659
The restroom is that way.

104
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:56,840
Thank you.

105
00:05:57,530 --> 00:05:58,530
Uh...

106
00:05:58,810 --> 00:06:00,520
Have you eaten?

107
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:03,470
Would you like any appetizers?
Or maybe a whole meal to fill you up?

108
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,970
The kitchen is actually closed,
but I can reopen it

109
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:07,390
since I'm the owner's little sister.

110
00:06:08,620 --> 00:06:09,370
It's okay.

111
00:06:10,610 --> 00:06:12,000
And what's your name again?

112
00:06:12,650 --> 00:06:13,550
It's Ployplern.

113
00:06:13,690 --> 00:06:15,920
You can call me Ploy or Plern.
Both are fine.

114
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:19,470
Can I have a photo with you?

115
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:20,590
Of course.

116
00:06:21,980 --> 00:06:24,160
Let's do a selfie.
Front camera photos mean you're close.

117
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:25,240
Alright.

118
00:06:25,630 --> 00:06:26,900
Let me take it.

119
00:06:30,020 --> 00:06:30,810
Ready?

120
00:06:35,780 --> 00:06:38,690
Pure, don't photobomb me!
We're taking a two-shot!

121
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:41,200
The more the merrier.

122
00:06:43,190 --> 00:06:44,000
All set?

123
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:49,990
There you go.

124
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,110
Thank you.

125
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:56,440
Here you go,

126
00:06:56,970 --> 00:06:58,790
our special recipe.

127
00:06:59,490 --> 00:07:01,600
This cocktail hasn't been named yet.

128
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:03,170
If you like it,

129
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:05,760
may I name it after you?

130
00:07:07,670 --> 00:07:08,600
I'd rather not.

131
00:07:12,490 --> 00:07:14,720
You know, my sister here

132
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:16,320
is your biggest fan.

133
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:19,000
She's been keeping up with your updates
as if she were the news agency herself.

134
00:07:21,970 --> 00:07:23,980
Right, I forgot to introduce myself.

135
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:26,390
My name is Pure.

136
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:27,880
I'm the owner of this bar.

137
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:31,700
Nice to meet you.

138
00:07:32,010 --> 00:07:32,920
I'm Pitcha.

139
00:07:33,740 --> 00:07:34,960
You don't have to introduce yourself.

140
00:07:35,260 --> 00:07:36,900
Everyone here knows you.

141
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:39,190
This is the first time I've met you,

142
00:07:39,390 --> 00:07:40,900
yet it feels like I see you every day.

143
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:43,830
This girl loves watching your videos.

144
00:07:45,430 --> 00:07:46,380
Thank you.

145
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,170
So when are you going back to Korea?

146
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:55,540
It's pushed off indefinitely.

147
00:07:56,630 --> 00:07:57,840
But your leg...

148
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,750
looks fine.

149
00:08:05,050 --> 00:08:06,250
Oh, so...

150
00:08:06,550 --> 00:08:09,550
you want to get your fortune told
because of this, don't you?

151
00:08:10,370 --> 00:08:12,700
I heard my friends
in Thailand talking about it,

152
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:13,800
so I thought I might give it a try.

153
00:08:15,290 --> 00:08:17,280
So you're a victim of social media trends.

154
00:08:17,850 --> 00:08:20,410
Pure, isn't it good enough that he's here?

155
00:08:21,670 --> 00:08:22,720
I'm booking you for
the first appointment.

156
00:08:22,810 --> 00:08:24,300
I'll get it sorted.

157
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,240
Then...

158
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:34,110
I'd better get going.

159
00:08:34,549 --> 00:08:35,549
I'll be back tomorrow.

160
00:08:36,130 --> 00:08:38,330
You can go ahead and get me the bill.
Is a bank transfer alright?

161
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,610
It's fine.

162
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:41,640
This one is on the house

163
00:08:41,940 --> 00:08:44,920
since you've given us the honor
of gracing our bar.

164
00:08:45,540 --> 00:08:47,590
Thank you, then.

165
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:51,090
Then... I'll see you tomorrow.

166
00:08:51,860 --> 00:08:52,460
Alright.

167
00:09:02,350 --> 00:09:05,570
Was he even real? Am I dreaming?!

168
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:07,890
He stepped foot into our bar!

169
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:10,410
There's more to freak out about.

170
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:12,810
I can smell chaos ensuing.

171
00:09:28,550 --> 00:09:29,420
We've arrived.

172
00:09:35,890 --> 00:09:37,230
Thank you.

173
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:41,560
Are you holding up alright?

174
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,860
Do you want me to walk you upstairs?

175
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:45,920
I'm alright.

176
00:09:46,590 --> 00:09:47,930
It's not like I'm drunk.

177
00:09:48,580 --> 00:09:49,580
Not drunk?

178
00:09:50,410 --> 00:09:53,110
You fell asleep and snored so loudly.

179
00:09:54,210 --> 00:09:56,890
Drunk? I'm not drunk.

180
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,220
I saw how much you drank,

181
00:10:00,790 --> 00:10:02,300
and you still insist you're not.

182
00:10:03,230 --> 00:10:05,820
I'm telling you that I'm not.

183
00:10:16,930 --> 00:10:18,510
Why are you doing this?

184
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,080
Doing what?

185
00:10:21,540 --> 00:10:23,710
Making me fall in love.

186
00:10:28,730 --> 00:10:29,730
Is it working?

187
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,660
Do you want me to walk you to your place?

188
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:15,890
Hah.

189
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:18,520
I know

190
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,360
what you're thinking about doing up there.

191
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,170
Walking you to your place, of course.

192
00:12:30,090 --> 00:12:31,640
No, no, no.

193
00:12:33,830 --> 00:12:35,570
I'm not falling for that.

194
00:12:39,710 --> 00:12:40,940
Falling for what?

195
00:12:41,420 --> 00:12:42,820
Who actually started it?

196
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,510
I'd better go.

197
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:49,990
Hold up.

198
00:12:51,050 --> 00:12:52,390
When do you want me to pick you up?

199
00:12:54,030 --> 00:12:55,030
To where?

200
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,440
To the university, of course.

201
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,610
I'm not going.

202
00:13:02,550 --> 00:13:04,700
I'll work on my assignments
at my place tomorrow.

203
00:13:06,530 --> 00:13:07,530
Then...

204
00:13:07,810 --> 00:13:09,010
I'll keep you company.

205
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:12,300
Do you even have time?

206
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:14,700
I sure do.

207
00:13:16,010 --> 00:13:17,020
I promise

208
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:18,960
I'll sit completely still.

209
00:13:19,110 --> 00:13:20,760
You won't even notice I'm there.

210
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:25,380
Mm.

211
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:37,640
Before bed,

212
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:40,770
send me a message, okay?

213
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:47,670
Got it.

214
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:49,910
Good night.

215
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:51,700
Mm.

216
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:40,610
Are you back at your place?

217
00:14:42,170 --> 00:14:43,890
Yes, sir.

218
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:49,390
Are you worried about me or afraid
your bar is missing a fortune teller?

219
00:14:50,450 --> 00:14:51,450
Do you have any idea

220
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:52,900
who was here looking for you

221
00:14:53,090 --> 00:14:54,810
after you left?

222
00:14:55,950 --> 00:14:57,240
How am I supposed to know that?

223
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:58,720
Who?

224
00:15:00,350 --> 00:15:01,350
The real one

225
00:15:01,710 --> 00:15:04,230
has come back to claim what's his.

226
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:37,680
Where were you so late?

227
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:42,810
Outside, Mom.

228
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:44,540
So where exactly?

229
00:15:46,210 --> 00:15:47,260
I was meeting some friends.

230
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:52,310
Do you have another
doctor's appointment tomorrow?

231
00:15:53,810 --> 00:15:55,500
Not until next week.

232
00:15:57,520 --> 00:16:00,020
Is your leg doing fine now?

233
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:03,360
It is, Mom.

234
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:06,790
What are you doing out here?
Why haven't you gone to bed?

235
00:16:07,420 --> 00:16:10,140
I saw that you weren't home yet,
so I was worried.

236
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:13,400
Then, please go to bed.

237
00:16:13,530 --> 00:16:15,000
I'll be taking a shower before bed.

238
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:18,130
If your leg is doing fine now,

239
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,520
you should get back to
your dance practices sometimes.

240
00:16:22,590 --> 00:16:23,550
Yes, Mom.

241
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:27,970
Good night.

242
00:16:56,380 --> 00:16:57,700
Oh, Itthi.

243
00:16:58,510 --> 00:16:59,480
Where are you heading out to?

244
00:16:59,650 --> 00:17:00,650
How about a meal first?

245
00:17:01,430 --> 00:17:02,560
I have something to attend to.

246
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,360
Hm?

247
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:04,390
I'm heading out now.

248
00:17:05,460 --> 00:17:07,130
This early in the morning?

249
00:17:07,210 --> 00:17:08,109
Right?

250
00:17:09,829 --> 00:17:12,000
Alright, once the incense burns out,
take down the offerings.

251
00:17:20,710 --> 00:17:24,760
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

252
00:17:24,790 --> 00:17:28,850
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

253
00:17:28,890 --> 00:17:30,990
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

254
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:36,560
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

255
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:41,720
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

256
00:17:41,750 --> 00:17:45,130
♫Slightly out of line,♫

257
00:17:45,990 --> 00:17:49,680
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

258
00:17:49,710 --> 00:17:54,020
♫Try answering
if your world will cross with mine♫

259
00:17:54,050 --> 00:17:58,100
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

260
00:17:58,130 --> 00:18:03,640
♫I believe our love will change our♫

261
00:18:03,670 --> 00:18:07,520
♫Destiny, rewrite prophecies♫

262
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:11,380
♫Even if they are against our destiny♫

263
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:14,360
♫(But we're gonna try… try… try!)♫

264
00:18:14,390 --> 00:18:20,150
♫And I believe our love has power♫

265
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:24,000
♫I believe the love of us♫

266
00:18:24,030 --> 00:18:31,960
♫Will realign the stars back
to the line where they should be♫

267
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:35,300
♫(And we're gonna try… try… try!)♫

268
00:18:39,650 --> 00:18:40,510
Hey,

269
00:18:41,050 --> 00:18:42,090
are you almost done

270
00:18:42,650 --> 00:18:44,200
so you can finally get in the pool with me?

271
00:18:46,390 --> 00:18:47,740
Quit bugging!

272
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:50,050
I'm trying to focus on my work here.

273
00:18:55,500 --> 00:18:59,550
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

274
00:18:59,580 --> 00:19:05,090
♫I believe our love will change our♫

275
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:08,970
♫Destiny, rewrite prophecies♫

276
00:19:09,010 --> 00:19:13,130
♫Even if they are against our destiny♫

277
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:16,190
♫(But we're gonna try… try… try!)♫

278
00:20:03,340 --> 00:20:04,410
Let's go. Kick your legs.

279
00:20:06,810 --> 00:20:08,570
Coach, I'm gonna head out now.

280
00:20:08,820 --> 00:20:09,820
- Bye.
- Bye now.

281
00:20:09,930 --> 00:20:11,910
Oh! Itthiphumi,
are you forgetting your phone?

282
00:20:12,540 --> 00:20:14,090
Uh... My phone is right here.

283
00:20:15,730 --> 00:20:17,320
Hey, double-check it.

284
00:20:24,980 --> 00:20:27,990
Excuse me, that's my phone.

285
00:21:05,230 --> 00:21:06,090
Where are you now?

286
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:07,730
Your querents are here waiting.

287
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:09,470
I'm not coming in tonight.

288
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:11,400
Still not caught up with my work.

289
00:21:11,910 --> 00:21:13,960
You're scared
to meet his real sweetheart?

290
00:21:14,860 --> 00:21:16,560
Man, he's good-looking.

291
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:19,290
I think that if they eventually meet...

292
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:20,540
Oh! Hey,

293
00:21:21,430 --> 00:21:23,660
what are you saying?
I can't hear you.

294
00:21:23,690 --> 00:21:25,860
Pure, the reception is bad.

295
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,810
I have to go.

296
00:21:29,460 --> 00:21:31,080
Is Ritt almost here?

297
00:21:31,350 --> 00:21:32,390
Master Ritt just bailed.

298
00:21:32,580 --> 00:21:33,080
What?

299
00:21:33,140 --> 00:21:34,120
No whats.

300
00:21:34,310 --> 00:21:37,350
We have never told the customers
that Ritt would come in every day.

301
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:44,960
But you already told that new customer

302
00:21:45,040 --> 00:21:46,710
to come to Ritt today.

303
00:21:55,060 --> 00:21:56,240
I'm not late

304
00:21:56,670 --> 00:21:57,870
for today's first appointment, am I?

305
00:21:58,470 --> 00:22:00,630
Uh... So...

306
00:22:01,650 --> 00:22:02,650
You're not.

307
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:03,720
But...

308
00:22:03,900 --> 00:22:05,030
do you mind waiting?

309
00:22:07,530 --> 00:22:09,160
Are you in a hurry tonight?

310
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:10,680
Why?

311
00:22:10,910 --> 00:22:13,110
I have a new cocktail recipe
for you to try.

312
00:22:13,260 --> 00:22:14,200
Are you interested?

313
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:20,840
Was that Pure calling?

314
00:22:25,690 --> 00:22:26,420
Mm.

315
00:22:26,740 --> 00:22:27,740
But I told him

316
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:29,370
that I wasn't going in.

317
00:22:30,770 --> 00:22:31,590
Are you tired?

318
00:22:33,130 --> 00:22:35,170
I just want to get my work done.

319
00:22:35,660 --> 00:22:38,210
I need to report a progress update
with the professor tomorrow.

320
00:22:39,310 --> 00:22:40,880
I'll take you to meet
my Grandpa and Grandma later.

321
00:22:41,590 --> 00:22:44,640
My family believes
in superstition, feng shui, energy,

322
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:46,640
and Chinese space layout.

323
00:22:46,730 --> 00:22:49,010
There are around
ten feng shui masters in our company.

324
00:22:51,940 --> 00:22:52,750
Sure.

325
00:22:53,310 --> 00:22:55,990
I might get some insights from the experts.

326
00:22:58,630 --> 00:23:00,070
Grandpa and Grandma will like you

327
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,510
if you guys meet.

328
00:23:03,110 --> 00:23:03,970
Why?

329
00:23:05,130 --> 00:23:05,800
Well...

330
00:23:06,460 --> 00:23:07,460
If I like someone,

331
00:23:08,210 --> 00:23:09,490
my parents will like them as well.

332
00:23:12,990 --> 00:23:15,040
You're pretty good at flirting.

333
00:23:15,940 --> 00:23:17,310
Maybe if I keep flirting,

334
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:19,620
I might get to go
from a childhood sweetheart

335
00:23:20,570 --> 00:23:22,180
to something real one day.

336
00:23:31,040 --> 00:23:33,440
If we weren't sweethearts,

337
00:23:35,060 --> 00:23:36,510
it would've been hard
to approach you, huh?

338
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:39,640
Just a bit.

339
00:23:41,130 --> 00:23:43,300
I just don't have chemistry with anyone

340
00:23:43,940 --> 00:23:46,160
to click with out there.

341
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:50,930
Keep working.

342
00:23:52,270 --> 00:23:54,210
I'll visit again tomorrow.

343
00:23:56,420 --> 00:23:57,220
Okay.

344
00:23:58,250 --> 00:23:59,250
Drive safe.

345
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:39,320
Pitcha, are you hungry? Have you eaten?

346
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:40,490
Would you like to order anything?

347
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:41,840
We serve delicious food here.

348
00:24:42,030 --> 00:24:42,830
I'm good.

349
00:24:43,130 --> 00:24:43,870
Thank you.

350
00:24:43,990 --> 00:24:45,920
You have to be on a diet, right?

351
00:24:45,950 --> 00:24:47,690
I watched Jinha's interview.

352
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:49,160
They really ate so little.

353
00:24:49,230 --> 00:24:50,490
When will Master Ritt be here?

354
00:24:51,690 --> 00:24:52,620
Oh...

355
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:54,120
Here,

356
00:24:54,820 --> 00:24:55,880
'Oppa on the Rock.'

357
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:57,700
I just came up with the name,

358
00:24:58,230 --> 00:24:59,590
inspired by...

359
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:02,070
a Thai idol who rose to stardom overseas.

360
00:25:02,590 --> 00:25:03,590
Better hurry and give it a taste.

361
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:06,770
It's one of a kind.
So unique that no one can recreate it.

362
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:08,720
We couldn't,
even if you ask for it next time.

363
00:25:08,950 --> 00:25:11,270
That's too much, sis.

364
00:25:12,610 --> 00:25:13,680
Give it a go.

365
00:25:13,990 --> 00:25:16,680
I'm open to feedback about the taste.

366
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:23,000
Ugh!

367
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:24,500
Hey!

368
00:25:24,730 --> 00:25:26,770
What did you put in it?
Why is it so strong?

369
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:28,270
Lots of things.

370
00:25:28,490 --> 00:25:29,630
But the most important of all

371
00:25:29,870 --> 00:25:31,100
is that I poured my heart into it.

372
00:25:31,610 --> 00:25:33,250
That explains why it's bitter.

373
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,220
Burn!

374
00:25:39,150 --> 00:25:39,830
So...

375
00:25:40,270 --> 00:25:41,560
what is bothering you so bad

376
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:43,250
that you want to have
your fortune read with Master Ritt?

377
00:25:51,130 --> 00:25:53,450
- Does it hurt?
- No, you're doing great.

378
00:25:53,930 --> 00:25:55,190
My shins feel stiff.

379
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:03,820
Grandma.

380
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:08,120
You left so early and came home this late?

381
00:26:08,660 --> 00:26:10,380
What have you been out for?

382
00:26:13,710 --> 00:26:15,300
Jeez...

383
00:26:15,340 --> 00:26:17,120
Why are you still up, Grandma?

384
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:19,080
That could really age you.

385
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:21,560
You haven't answered my question.

386
00:26:21,810 --> 00:26:24,510
Judging from how you act,
are you dating someone?

387
00:26:24,900 --> 00:26:28,420
Who's that poor one
unlucky enough to have you as a boyfriend?

388
00:26:29,510 --> 00:26:30,930
Jeez, Grandma.

389
00:26:31,490 --> 00:26:32,490
They're the lucky one.

390
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:34,740
So there's really someone?

391
00:26:37,810 --> 00:26:39,010
Is there?

392
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:40,950
Let me take a look.

393
00:26:41,150 --> 00:26:44,440
You look strangely cheerful these days.

394
00:26:44,710 --> 00:26:46,290
You're barely home at that.

395
00:26:48,930 --> 00:26:50,090
If you meet them,

396
00:26:50,490 --> 00:26:51,490
you're gonna like them.

397
00:26:51,970 --> 00:26:53,200
Really now?

398
00:26:54,450 --> 00:26:55,760
I want to meet them.

399
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:58,780
I wanna know what they're like.
Would you bring them home?

400
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:02,720
You're already in a relationship.

401
00:27:02,850 --> 00:27:04,350
Don't be all affectionate now.

402
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:15,950
Ploy,

403
00:27:16,430 --> 00:27:17,610
that table wants their bill.

404
00:27:17,990 --> 00:27:18,910
You go.

405
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:21,510
You go, so you can get a tip.

406
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:32,160
You're nothing like I imagined.

407
00:27:32,830 --> 00:27:34,860
When I first saw you on the news,

408
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:36,710
in those videos Ploy showed me,

409
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:40,160
I thought you were someone
so perfect that you were flawless,

410
00:27:40,260 --> 00:27:41,320
down to the finest detail.

411
00:27:42,630 --> 00:27:43,960
But when I actually see you...

412
00:27:45,980 --> 00:27:46,980
You're completely different
from what I thought.

413
00:27:47,850 --> 00:27:48,850
What am I like in person?

414
00:27:49,130 --> 00:27:51,220
You seem like an ordinary guy.

415
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:52,460
Except that...

416
00:27:52,890 --> 00:27:53,900
you're good-looking

417
00:27:54,330 --> 00:27:55,330
with a great body,

418
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:56,810
great skin,

419
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:58,040
beautiful eyes,

420
00:27:58,940 --> 00:28:00,030
luscious hair,

421
00:28:00,370 --> 00:28:02,760
- and...
- That's still ordinary, right?

422
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:08,720
And...

423
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:11,750
you seem more genuine
than I saw in videos.

424
00:28:15,550 --> 00:28:16,560
Living there

425
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:18,490
must be so draining for you.

426
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:22,220
I saw nothing but one
practice video after another.

427
00:28:23,130 --> 00:28:23,900
Yes,

428
00:28:24,820 --> 00:28:25,940
I trained very hard

429
00:28:27,110 --> 00:28:28,200
and barely got any sleep.

430
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:31,250
I have to bear the
pressure every day,

431
00:28:32,660 --> 00:28:33,710
and in the end...

432
00:28:35,930 --> 00:28:37,240
I didn't even get to debut.

433
00:28:38,110 --> 00:28:39,800
But you can still smile.

434
00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:42,710
Probably because if I hadn't been smiling,

435
00:28:43,990 --> 00:28:45,350
I would’ve been on the ground by now.

436
00:28:50,970 --> 00:28:51,620
I think...

437
00:28:52,350 --> 00:28:54,350
you're a lot better
than you think you are.

438
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:56,900
Or maybe...

439
00:28:57,770 --> 00:28:59,900
I'm only like that in front of others.

440
00:29:01,660 --> 00:29:02,660
Your eyes

441
00:29:03,100 --> 00:29:04,180
really don't hide a single thing.

442
00:29:04,900 --> 00:29:05,610
Why?

443
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:08,040
Whatever you feel

444
00:29:08,700 --> 00:29:09,610
or think,

445
00:29:11,060 --> 00:29:12,790
I can tell when I look into your eyes.

446
00:29:16,060 --> 00:29:16,920
Let's give it a test.

447
00:29:22,970 --> 00:29:23,970
What do you think

448
00:29:24,380 --> 00:29:25,480
I'm thinking?

449
00:29:35,500 --> 00:29:38,110
Right now, you want a friend to talk to.

450
00:29:40,270 --> 00:29:43,450
You want someone who truly listens.

451
00:29:56,590 --> 00:29:58,210
And I...

452
00:29:58,620 --> 00:30:00,220
happen to be a good listener,

453
00:30:00,490 --> 00:30:01,440
in case you don't know.

454
00:30:02,020 --> 00:30:04,400
So... is Master Ritt still coming in?

455
00:30:07,670 --> 00:30:10,440
Ploy, call Master Ritt
and ask if he's almost here.

456
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:11,760
Oh,

457
00:30:12,190 --> 00:30:15,600
Ritt sent a message saying
he wasn't able to catch up with his work.

458
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:17,320
He won't be coming in anymore today.

459
00:30:20,210 --> 00:30:21,660
I think you've missed him.

460
00:30:21,750 --> 00:30:22,750
The wait was in vain.

461
00:30:23,900 --> 00:30:24,720
Not at all.

462
00:30:24,850 --> 00:30:26,900
Talking to you has been pretty fun.

463
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:29,140
I...

464
00:30:29,500 --> 00:30:30,900
just happen to be a big storyteller, too,

465
00:30:31,470 --> 00:30:32,530
in case you don't know.

466
00:30:50,700 --> 00:30:51,540
I won't give you any changes

467
00:30:51,700 --> 00:30:52,700
so that you will come back.

468
00:30:52,810 --> 00:30:55,180
Consider this a prepayment.

469
00:30:55,370 --> 00:30:56,370
If you don't come back,

470
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:57,910
it's your loss.

471
00:31:00,020 --> 00:31:00,740
Okay.

472
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:01,840
Then...

473
00:31:02,180 --> 00:31:03,210
Please excuse me.

474
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:04,840
See you again.

475
00:31:18,570 --> 00:31:19,290
What?

476
00:31:19,450 --> 00:31:20,370
I saw that.

477
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:40,070
♫And I believe our love has power♫

478
00:31:40,100 --> 00:31:43,900
♫I believe the love of us♫

479
00:31:43,940 --> 00:31:52,910
♫Will realign the stars back
to the line where they should be♫

480
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:57,950
Right, Itthi, since you have time,

481
00:31:58,100 --> 00:31:59,370
come to the company with me.

482
00:31:59,430 --> 00:32:01,690
They said there would be
a new presentation for the new project.

483
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:03,490
That way, you can give me a hand.

484
00:32:03,610 --> 00:32:07,120
I have some chicken braised,
and I'm going to make shou mian.

485
00:32:07,210 --> 00:32:10,800
Then I'll have the chauffeur
deliver it to you two for lunch.

486
00:32:10,940 --> 00:32:13,750
- I...
- Right, and change into a suit because

487
00:32:13,790 --> 00:32:14,860
this looks way too young.

488
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:16,790
It has to be a distinguished look, alright?

489
00:32:16,810 --> 00:32:17,960
Of course, Grandpa.

490
00:32:18,510 --> 00:32:19,840
And tomorrow,

491
00:32:20,090 --> 00:32:22,010
there will be personnel from
an overseas company visiting us.

492
00:32:22,110 --> 00:32:23,870
They want to have a look
at the construction site.

493
00:32:24,450 --> 00:32:26,310
There. Take Itthi with you.

494
00:32:26,610 --> 00:32:28,630
- He's good at the language. He could help.
- Exactly.

495
00:32:28,660 --> 00:32:29,510
I was going to say that.

496
00:32:30,110 --> 00:32:33,020
From now on, you can demand
the salary from your grandfather.

497
00:32:33,060 --> 00:32:34,770
Don't work for him for free, alright?

498
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:38,910
Well, well, look at you egging him on.

499
00:33:19,930 --> 00:33:21,010
I'm sorry.

500
00:33:21,030 --> 00:33:25,360
I have to visit the company with Grandpa.
I won't be able to see you today.

501
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:33,850
It's fine. I was just thinking about
researching at the university.

502
00:33:34,330 --> 00:33:35,850
Will probably be there until dusk.

503
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:39,950
Stay focused.
Don't charm anyone, or I'll get jealous.

504
00:33:39,990 --> 00:33:45,580
There you go again. Is your family business
real estate or professional flirting?

505
00:34:04,730 --> 00:34:06,400
Is Ritt,
the Prophecy Stone Master, in today?

506
00:34:09,429 --> 00:34:10,280
Thank you.

507
00:34:11,330 --> 00:34:12,679
Hey! Wait.

508
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:15,600
I have a special cocktail for you today.

509
00:34:16,190 --> 00:34:17,750
It's the new and improved
Oppa on the Rock.

510
00:34:17,790 --> 00:34:19,080
Please test it for me.

511
00:34:21,310 --> 00:34:22,139
Please?

512
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:24,429
Just a little?

513
00:34:24,719 --> 00:34:25,500
Sure.

514
00:34:30,820 --> 00:34:31,600
Here you go,

515
00:34:31,940 --> 00:34:34,020
the new and improved Oppa on the Rock.

516
00:34:35,510 --> 00:34:36,420
Thank you.

517
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:45,070
Uh... On what days
does Master Ritt usually come in?

518
00:35:14,030 --> 00:35:15,030
Here,

519
00:35:15,300 --> 00:35:18,210
for a lady like you,
I believe you'll enjoy the sweetness.

520
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:20,240
I recommend 'Red Pomegranate,'

521
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:26,170
Is Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master
coming in today?

522
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:29,950
He hasn't shown up just yet.

523
00:35:31,380 --> 00:35:33,460
I actually called him,

524
00:35:33,540 --> 00:35:34,710
but he didn't pick up.

525
00:35:35,110 --> 00:35:37,120
Anyway, would you care for a drink?

526
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:39,720
Uh...

527
00:35:40,860 --> 00:35:41,550
Sure.

528
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:44,840
But you'll give him another call, right?

529
00:35:45,750 --> 00:35:46,830
Sure thing.

530
00:35:47,310 --> 00:35:48,680
I'll give him another call.

531
00:36:24,910 --> 00:36:26,070
How about this?

532
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:28,210
Can I have your number?

533
00:36:28,740 --> 00:36:30,650
Whenever he comes in,

534
00:36:30,690 --> 00:36:32,020
I'll give you a call.

535
00:36:38,390 --> 00:36:41,840
Would you mind
putting your number on my phone, Pitcha?

536
00:36:58,080 --> 00:36:59,950
Now, we both have each other's numbers.

537
00:37:00,180 --> 00:37:00,930
So...

538
00:37:01,780 --> 00:37:03,570
when do you have time

539
00:37:03,870 --> 00:37:05,530
for me to give you a call?

540
00:37:06,890 --> 00:37:08,400
About Master Ritt, right?

541
00:37:09,790 --> 00:37:11,160
Of course.

542
00:37:11,370 --> 00:37:12,170
And...

543
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:15,440
maybe about something else, too.

544
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:19,480
It'd be great to know
the appropriate time to call.

545
00:37:19,640 --> 00:37:20,980
Anytime.

546
00:37:21,450 --> 00:37:22,360
If I have time, I'll pick up.

547
00:37:22,820 --> 00:37:24,040
If I don't have time, I won't pick up.

548
00:37:25,030 --> 00:37:26,550
So you're saying I can call?

549
00:37:33,100 --> 00:37:36,630
Grandpa asked me
to go to the site with him.

550
00:37:36,710 --> 00:37:39,920
That's the fourth day
we won't get to see each other.

551
00:37:42,210 --> 00:37:45,980
You're not using work
as an excuse to ditch me, right?

552
00:37:47,670 --> 00:37:50,990
Who'd ditch you?
I'm missing you to death now.

553
00:38:03,210 --> 00:38:06,700
Calculating the value of the building
offered to us for sale this afternoon?

554
00:38:06,930 --> 00:38:08,750
I saw you multiply something
by a hundred or a thousand there.

555
00:38:08,900 --> 00:38:09,900
Uh...

556
00:38:10,600 --> 00:38:11,910
Yes, Grandpa.

557
00:38:12,460 --> 00:38:14,660
What do you think
the number should be multiplied by?

558
00:38:14,700 --> 00:38:16,630
I think that would be...

559
00:38:19,140 --> 00:38:20,580
too little...

560
00:38:23,940 --> 00:38:25,220
Let's go with this number.

561
00:39:04,090 --> 00:39:05,500
My beloved buddy,

562
00:39:05,750 --> 00:39:08,080
could you enlighten me
in regards to your whereabouts?

563
00:39:08,110 --> 00:39:11,070
You are immensely needed by the bar.

564
00:39:11,960 --> 00:39:12,940
Uh...

565
00:39:13,490 --> 00:39:14,490
I...

566
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:16,070
If it's about Pitcha,

567
00:39:16,410 --> 00:39:17,760
I've taken care of it.

568
00:39:21,020 --> 00:39:22,190
How did you do that?

569
00:39:22,520 --> 00:39:23,760
I told him that

570
00:39:23,790 --> 00:39:25,540
if he still wants
his fortune read by you,

571
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:26,940
I'll give him a call.

572
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:30,070
That means as long as I don't,
he's not gonna show up.

573
00:39:30,410 --> 00:39:31,620
In short,

574
00:39:31,780 --> 00:39:33,350
I solved your problem.

575
00:39:33,560 --> 00:39:35,580
So would you, my dear friend,

576
00:39:35,650 --> 00:39:38,000
be so kind as to grace my bar?

577
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:40,220
While I was away,

578
00:39:40,550 --> 00:39:41,550
how is the bar doing?

579
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:43,540
The sale dropped to some degree.

580
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:47,800
That's why I'm trying everything
to get you to service your fans.

581
00:39:48,040 --> 00:39:49,960
I told them
that you were definitely coming back,

582
00:39:50,080 --> 00:39:51,710
but I just didn't know when,

583
00:39:51,730 --> 00:39:53,000
and that it was all in the master's hands.

584
00:39:55,270 --> 00:39:56,440
Alright, alright.

585
00:39:56,900 --> 00:39:58,880
I've been bored lately.

586
00:39:59,140 --> 00:40:00,000
Gotta go.

587
00:40:00,130 --> 00:40:01,560
I'm going in tonight.

588
00:40:04,650 --> 00:40:06,590
Thank you so much, my friend.

589
00:40:06,620 --> 00:40:07,690
I myself

590
00:40:07,720 --> 00:40:09,970
will prepare a nice drink to welcome you.

591
00:40:10,310 --> 00:40:11,450
Alright.

592
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:12,810
See you.

593
00:40:24,150 --> 00:40:26,860
If this whole thing pans out to be good,

594
00:40:27,330 --> 00:40:29,650
it will be obvious to your eyes.

595
00:40:30,430 --> 00:40:32,690
But if it's not getting better,

596
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:35,480
that means it needs fixing.

597
00:40:36,410 --> 00:40:41,300
And there's no one for that but...

598
00:40:41,340 --> 00:40:42,160
you!

599
00:40:42,740 --> 00:40:44,350
The one who will fix it!

600
00:40:46,220 --> 00:40:47,180
Thank you.

601
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:01,370
A heart...

602
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:03,470
can't be controlled.

603
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:08,330
If they are to love,
it's because they genuinely feel for you.

604
00:41:10,310 --> 00:41:12,130
But if they don't,

605
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:14,590
you can't force them to do anything.

606
00:41:14,900 --> 00:41:16,760
See, girl? Told you so.

607
00:41:17,260 --> 00:41:18,370
Do you believe me now?

608
00:41:19,690 --> 00:41:20,960
Do your best!

609
00:41:21,140 --> 00:41:22,430
And wait to see what happens.

610
00:41:22,930 --> 00:41:25,890
If you're right for each other,

611
00:41:26,650 --> 00:41:29,470
you will know from how they respond.

612
00:41:30,390 --> 00:41:31,390
Don't rush it!

613
00:41:32,280 --> 00:41:33,690
Give yourself some time.

614
00:41:33,870 --> 00:41:34,870
Do the same for them.

615
00:41:36,730 --> 00:41:37,650
Thank you.

616
00:41:42,890 --> 00:41:44,580
Here you go.
This one is gonna be very strong.

617
00:41:46,570 --> 00:41:48,950
Is that the last one, Ployplern?

618
00:41:48,990 --> 00:41:49,810
That's right.

619
00:41:49,850 --> 00:41:53,580
That was quite a lot on your plate.
They knew you came, so they all rushed in.

620
00:41:53,830 --> 00:41:55,800
Easy peasy.

621
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:20,170
Didn't you tell me
that you'd give me a call

622
00:42:20,460 --> 00:42:21,470
if Master Ritt would come?

623
00:42:23,550 --> 00:42:24,310
Well...

624
00:42:24,790 --> 00:42:26,770
how did you know he was here?

625
00:42:28,350 --> 00:42:30,220
I saw some posts that tagged the bar.

626
00:42:32,920 --> 00:42:33,920
Pure,

627
00:42:34,240 --> 00:42:35,240
since I'm all done with the slots,

628
00:42:35,270 --> 00:42:36,270
I'm heading out.

629
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:37,720
I'm not gonna wait for the bar to close.

630
00:42:40,460 --> 00:42:42,270
Are you Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master?

631
00:42:48,950 --> 00:42:50,540
Do you mind taking another customer?

632
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:21,560
The ceremony has finished.

633
00:43:22,630 --> 00:43:25,560
But I looked into
the astrological calendar,

634
00:43:25,590 --> 00:43:27,710
and it didn't mention
any ceremony that has to be performed.

635
00:43:28,810 --> 00:43:31,090
It's newly emerged.

636
00:43:31,490 --> 00:43:33,570
This ceremony
will bless you with prosperity!

637
00:43:33,700 --> 00:43:35,180
Yes, prosperity!

638
00:43:36,050 --> 00:43:39,120
The Romani art also states the same.

639
00:43:39,150 --> 00:43:42,640
The Lanna said, a ceremony
performed during the night

640
00:43:42,740 --> 00:43:44,270
will be favored!

641
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:48,720
Do I make offerings
at the shrine tomorrow morning?

642
00:43:49,070 --> 00:43:51,360
You still have to.

643
00:43:51,720 --> 00:43:52,840
Sure, sure.

644
00:43:52,880 --> 00:43:56,040
- As for the supply and ceremony fee...
- Right!

645
00:43:56,090 --> 00:43:58,240
- Could I...
- Give me the total.

646
00:43:58,270 --> 00:44:00,600
I'll take care of it, alright?

647
00:44:01,100 --> 00:44:02,300
- Sure, sure.
- Come on.

648
00:44:02,340 --> 00:44:04,240
Let's go inside.

649
00:44:04,720 --> 00:44:05,610
Itthi,

650
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:08,670
do you have to help your grandpa
at the company tomorrow?

651
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:11,200
Uh, he said that I didn't have to.

652
00:44:11,660 --> 00:44:14,200
He has a meeting with his friend
about the land near Rangsit.

653
00:44:15,490 --> 00:44:18,560
Well, well, I can see sparks flying
from your eyes from not having to work.

654
00:44:19,760 --> 00:44:21,200
How about this? Tomorrow,

655
00:44:21,230 --> 00:44:24,240
would you come with me to the old market
to help me carry my stuff?

656
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:27,360
You have three people
to help you with your stuff.

657
00:44:27,710 --> 00:44:29,020
I'll sit this one out.

658
00:44:29,990 --> 00:44:31,140
So where are you going?

659
00:44:33,450 --> 00:44:34,220
Hm?

660
00:44:34,820 --> 00:44:36,530
Why are you bugging the kid?

661
00:44:37,060 --> 00:44:39,150
He looks strangely lively!

662
00:44:39,200 --> 00:44:40,650
Are you jealous?

663
00:44:42,190 --> 00:44:43,440
We'd better get inside, Grandma.

664
00:44:44,720 --> 00:44:46,900
Alright, come on. Let's get inside.

665
00:44:54,630 --> 00:44:56,100
Anything else you want to ask,

666
00:44:56,150 --> 00:44:58,250
besides your career in Korea?

667
00:44:59,630 --> 00:45:00,440
There is.

668
00:45:01,900 --> 00:45:03,230
What do you want to ask the stones about?

669
00:45:07,290 --> 00:45:08,290
Love.

670
00:45:10,370 --> 00:45:12,070
Concentrate deeply.

671
00:45:12,320 --> 00:45:14,990
Set your mind on what you wish to ask.

672
00:45:16,120 --> 00:45:18,640
These stones reveal the reality

673
00:45:19,070 --> 00:45:21,530
and settle your doubts according to...

674
00:45:23,840 --> 00:45:24,840
the prophecy.

675
00:45:26,600 --> 00:45:28,260
Close your eyes

676
00:45:28,560 --> 00:45:30,210
and pick three stones.

677
00:46:00,900 --> 00:46:02,170
What is your query?

678
00:46:04,470 --> 00:46:05,820
I want to know

679
00:46:06,130 --> 00:46:08,240
if the person who stood by me in the past

680
00:46:09,720 --> 00:46:11,910
will return to me.

681
00:46:38,220 --> 00:46:39,710
You should move on.

682
00:46:41,030 --> 00:46:42,640
He's never coming back to you.

683
00:47:07,330 --> 00:47:09,630
Was your prediction

684
00:47:09,660 --> 00:47:11,910
a result of a conflict of interest?

685
00:47:12,740 --> 00:47:14,610
Within three days,

686
00:47:15,280 --> 00:47:19,160
there will be little omens as a warning.

687
00:47:20,080 --> 00:47:20,870
Ow!

688
00:47:21,540 --> 00:47:23,990
I think... I'm gonna quit fortune-telling.

689
00:47:24,090 --> 00:47:25,190
Why is that?

690
00:47:25,230 --> 00:47:26,880
I feel like everything
is getting out of hand.

691
00:47:27,920 --> 00:47:29,140
Can you give me a hand?

692
00:47:31,120 --> 00:47:32,390
We're stuck inside.

693
00:47:32,530 --> 00:47:33,460
Please open the door.

694
00:47:33,490 --> 00:47:34,720
Can anybody hear me?

695
00:47:45,460 --> 00:47:49,510
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

696
00:47:49,540 --> 00:47:53,600
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

697
00:47:53,640 --> 00:47:55,740
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

698
00:47:55,800 --> 00:48:01,310
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

699
00:48:02,110 --> 00:48:06,470
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

700
00:48:06,500 --> 00:48:09,880
♫Slightly out of line,♫

701
00:48:10,740 --> 00:48:14,430
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

702
00:48:14,460 --> 00:48:18,770
♫Try answering if your world
will cross with mine♫

703
00:48:18,800 --> 00:48:22,850
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

704
00:48:22,880 --> 00:48:28,390
♫I believe our love will change our♫

705
00:48:28,420 --> 00:48:32,270
♫Destiny, rewrite prophecies♫

706
00:48:32,310 --> 00:48:36,430
♫Even if they are against our destiny♫

707
00:48:36,460 --> 00:48:39,110
♫(But we're gonna try… try… try!)♫

708
00:48:39,140 --> 00:48:44,900
♫And I believe our love has power♫

709
00:48:44,950 --> 00:48:48,750
♫I believe the love of us♫

710
00:48:48,780 --> 00:48:57,040
♫Will realign the stars back
to the line where they should be♫

711
00:48:57,080 --> 00:49:00,050
♫(And we're gonna try… try… try!)♫
